One common issue is the comparison of different instruments such as GAD-7 and SEFG. GAD-7, the Generalised Anxiety Disorder Assessment, is a seven-item instrument intended to measure the severity of generalised anxiety disorder. SEFG, on the other hand, is the Questionnaire for Head Teacher which comprises of multiple questions addressing various aspects of a school and student body.
